sentences: William Mitchell Byers (May 1, 1927 - May 1, 1996) was an American jazz trombonist and arranger.
Byers was born in Los Angeles on May 1, 1927.
He picked up trombone and played with Karl Kiffe before serving in the Army in 1944–45.

sentences: In the second half of the 1940s he arranged and played trombone for Georgie Auld, Buddy Rich, Benny Goodman, Charlie Ventura, and Teddy Powell.
Following this he composed for WMGM (AM) radio and television in New York City.
In the middle of the 1950s he was in Paris arranging; he also led a session of his own, released as Jazz on the Left Bank, at this time.
Later in the 1950s in Europe he played with Harold Arlen (1959–1960) and with the orchestra of Quincy Jones.
Later in the 1950s in Europe he played with Harold Arlen (1959–1960) and with the orchestra of Quincy Jones.
He became Jones's assistant at Mercury Records in the 1960s, and arranged for Count Basie albums.
He toured Europe and Japan alongside Frank Sinatra in 1974.
Byers died in Malibu, California, on May 1, 1996.
